This%20conversation%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20August%2C%20you%20wrote%20for%20the%20first%20time%20about%20your%20belief%20that%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Fsep%2F12%2Fyou-may-have-been-poisoned-how-an-independent-russian-journalist-became-a-target%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3Eyou%20were%20poisoned%20in%20Germany%20last%20Autumn%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E.%20How%20are%20you%20doing%20health-wise%20these%20days%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20feel%20much%20better%2C%20thank%20you.%20Almost%20all%20my%20symptoms%20are%20gone.%20The%20rest%20I%20have%20is%20just%20fatigue.%20I%20get%20tired%20very%20easily%20and%20it's%20actually%20irritating%20because%20I%20used%20to%20work%20a%20lot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20define%20myself%20through%20my%20work%20and%20it's%20really%20hard%20to%20understand%20that%20I%20have%20limits%20now%20and%20to%20recognize%20these%20limits.%20So%20I%20need%20some%20more%20time%20to%20deal%20with%20myself%2C%20I%20guess.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYour%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20Love%20Russia%2C%26quot%3B%20will%20be%20published%20in%20October.%20Are%20there%20any%20concerns%20that%20the%20book's%20publication%20could%20heighten%20your%20already%20high-level%20safety%20concerns%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20German%20police%20who%20are%20running%20the%20investigation%20said%20an%20international%20book%20release%20could%20be%20a%20trigger%20for%20the%20people%20who%20tried%20to%20do%20this%20to%20me.%20So%20yeah%2C%20I%20have%20some%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20quite%20an%20usual%20situation%20for%20me.%20When%20you%20work%20as%20an%20investigative%20reporter%20in%20Russia%2C%20you%20always%20want%20to%20publish%20something%20that%20your%20government%20doesn't%20want%20to%20be%20published.%20It's%20all%20just%20mind%20games%20because%20you%20never%20can%20evaluate%20the%20real%20danger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20time%20at%20Novaya%2C%20I%20got%20used%20to%20being%20concentrated%20on%20things%20you%20can%20change%20and%20not%20to%20go%20deep%20into%20the%20things%20you%20cannot%20change.%20I%20mean%20there%20are%20some%20basic%20and%20not%20so%20basic%20security%20protocols%20I've%20been%20following%2C%20but%20it's%20all%20that%20I%20can%20actually%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wrote%20a%20text%20and%20I%20want%20people%20to%20read%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Novaya%20Gazeta%20newspaper%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652ec452211def8ed83763f7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKostyuchenko%20started%20as%20an%20intern%20at%20Novaya%20Gazeta%20before%20joining%20as%20the%20newspaper's%20youngest%20ever%20staff%20member.%20%3Cp%3EPhoto%20by%20Alexander%20Welscher%2Fpicture%20alliance%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20you%20say%20where%20you%20are%20currently%3F%20Are%20you%20in%20hiding%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20moving%20a%20lot.%20That's%20all%20that%20I%20can%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI'm%20curious%20about%20the%20timing%20of%20how%20your%20book%20came%20together.%20When%20did%20you%20first%20start%20writing%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20first%20got%20the%20idea%20that%20I%20should%20write%20this%20book%2C%20I%20believe%20it%20was%20four%20years%20ago.%20It%20was%20just%20the%20first%20feeling%20that%20I%20needed%20to%20write%2C%20but%20as%20a%20full-time%20reporter%2C%20you%20always%20have%20things%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20at%20the%20end%20of%20February%2C%20Russia%20invaded%20Ukraine.%20So%2C%20I%20went%20back%20to%20Ukraine%20to%20work%20and%20I%20was%20working%20there%20for%20five%20weeks%20before%20I%20left%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20in%20very%20bad%20shape.%20I%20had%20lice%20and%20PTSD.%20I%20don't%20really%20remember%20the%20first%20four%20weeks%20after%20I%20left%20Ukraine.%20My%20girlfriend%20was%20with%20me%20so%20she%20was%20taking%20care%20of%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20I%20opened%20the%20internet%20and%20I%20started%20to%20look%20at%20what%20people%20were%20writing%20about%20Russia%2C%20what%20Western%20politicians%20were%20saying%20about%20Russia.%20I%20found%20out%20that%20their%20understanding%20of%20Russia%20is%20very%20poor%2C%20that%20people%20don't%20know%20what%20we%20are%20dealing%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20thought%20I%20cannot%20delay%20this%20anymore.%20I%20need%20to%20write.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20girlfriend%20became%20my%20first%20reader.%20She%20also%20took%20care%20of%20all%20other%20things%20for%20me%20like%20food%2C%20documents%2C%20cleaning%20the%20apartment%2C%20looking%20out%20for%20me%2C%20checking%20if%20I%20am%20eating%2C%20am%20I%20drinking%20and%20am%20I%20sleeping%3F%20And%20I%20was%20just%20writing%2C%20writing%2C%20writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDid%20you%20see%20any%20parallels%20to%20the%20current%20conflict%20in%20Ukraine%20as%20you%20were%20writing%20and%20revisiting%20your%20past%20reporting%20on%20Russia%3F%20I'm%20thinking%20specifically%20about%20the%20chapter%20that%20includes%20your%20reporting%20from%20the%20Donbas%20in%202014%20or%20the%20chapter%20about%20the%20northern%20Nganasan%20people%20who%20were%20%26quot%3Btamed%26quot%3B%20by%20Russia%20through%20the%20eradication%20of%20their%20language%20and%20culture.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20hoped%20that%20the%20story%20of%20the%20Nganasan%20and%20their%20disappearing%20nation%20would%20help%20Russians%20think%20about%20how%20many%20nations%20have%20already%20disappeared%2C%20how%20many%20cultures%2C%20and%20languages%2C%20and%20families%2C%20and%20traditions%2C%20and%20peoples%20as%20we%20are%20fighting%20with%20the%20Ukrainians%20to%20%26quot%3Bprotect%20the%20Russian%20language.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20new%20Russian%20fascism%20has%20grown%20into%20this%20nostalgia%20of%20the%20nice%2C%20old%2C%20Soviet%20days.%20For%20me%2C%20the%20key%20to%20understanding%20it%20was%20my%20mother%20who%20is%20a%20total%20Soviet%20woman%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20grief%20and%20sorrow%20about%20the%20Soviet%20Union%2C%20who%20still%20can't%20get%20over%20the%20idea%20that%20Kyiv%20is%20not%20our%20city%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPutin%20and%20his%20propaganda%2C%20they're%20using%20this%20nostalgia%20in%20the%20worst%20possible%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mother's%20generation%20think%20of%20themselves%20as%20victims%20because%20they%20lived%20in%20a%20country%20which%20they%20loved%20and%20this%20country%20was%20taken%20from%20them.%20They're%20not%20the%20ones%20who%20voted%20for%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20to%20be%20taken%20apart.%20It%20was%20politicians%20who%20made%20the%20decision%20and%2C%20in%20many%20ways%2C%20they%20still%20feel%20that%20they%20are%20victims%20and%20they%20feel%20grief%20about%20their%20past.%20So%20this%20longingness%20somehow%20became%20the%20reason%20for%20justifying%20killings%20happening%20in%20Ukraine.%20It's%20all%20quite%20crazy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22This%20photograph%20taken%20on%20on%20June%2012%2C%202023%20shows%20the%20Russian%20national%20flag%20next%20to%20a%20sculpture%20at%20the%20All-Russia%20Exhibition%20Centre%20(VDNKh)%2C%20a%20trade%20show%20and%20amusement%20park%20in%20Moscow%20during%20the%20Russia%20Day%20celebration.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652ec65796f7540cd05ea1de%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKostyuchenko%20left%20Russia%20to%20report%20on%20Ukraine%20soon%20after%20the%20war%20started.%20She%20has%20not%20been%20able%20to%20return%20to%20her%20home%20country.%20%3Cp%3EPhoto%20by%20KIRILL%20KUDRYAVTSEV%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20said%20you%20wrote%20this%20book%20primarily%20for%20Russians.%20As%20you%20look%20to%20the%20future%2C%20what%20do%20you%20see%20and%20hope%20for%20Russia%20and%20your%20people%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wrote%20the%20book%20for%20Russians%2C%20but%20not%20just%20for%20Russians%2C%20because%20I%20honestly%20believe%20that%20no%20country%20is%20immune%20from%20fascism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20so%20sure%20that%20we%20are%20immune%20because%20for%20Christ's%20sake%2C%20we%20fought%20the%20fascists!%20My%20grandfather%20did.%20We%20have%20this%20in%20textbooks%20in%20schools%3B%20we%20have%20whole%20movies%20telling%20us%20how%20fascism%20works%2C%20why%20it's%20so%20dangerous%2C%20and%20how%20it%20goes%20from%20a%20nice%20narrative%20to%20mass%20murders.%20I%20was%20totally%20sure%20we%20were%20immune.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20right%20now%2C%20with%20what's%20happening%20in%20the%20world%2C%20with%20this%20turn%20toward%20global%20authoritarianism%20and%20the%20tendencies%20you%20also%20have%20in%20your%20country%2C%20it's%20not%20safe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20could%20send%20a%20letter%20in%20the%20past%20to%20myself%2C%20I%20would%20say%3A%20%26quot%3BBe%20alarmed.%20Be%20alarmed.%20Don't%20be%20afraid%20to%20be%20hysterical.%20Be%20hysterical%20if%20you%20see%20your%20country%20is%20going%20into%20the%20darkness.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20really%20believe%20that%20this%20book%20would%20be%20useful%2C%20not%20just%20for%20people%20who%20want%20to%20understand%20what%20modern%20Russia%20is%20and%20how%20it%20became%20what%20it%20is%2C%20but%20also%20to%20understand%20how%20it's%20easy%20to%20lose%20your%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20girlfriend%20and%20I%20were%20just%20talking%20about%20the%20subtitle%20for%20the%20Russian%20version%20of%20the%20book%20and%20the%20subtitle%20my%20girlfriend%20gave%20is%20%26quot%3BHow%20to%20Fuck%20Up%20Your%20Country.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECertainly%20there%20are%20parallels%20within%20your%20reporting%20to%20things%20we've%20seen%20happening%20here%20in%20the%20US%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETotally.%20I%20honestly%20believe%20that%20you%20will%20take%20something%20from%20this%20book%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20have%20so%20much%20hope%20but%20this%20hope%20leaves%20you%20blind.%20The%20hope%20I%20have%20interferes%20in%20all%20my%20heart.%20I%20cannot%20really%20say%20that%20I%20see%20the%20future%20of%20Russia.%20I%20can%20say%20that%20I%20hope%20it%20will%20be%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20scenario%20for%20this%20to%20be%20possible%2C%20I%20believe%2C%20is%20if%20Russia%20loses%20in%20Ukraine.%20Because%20if%20Russia%2C%20God%20forbid%2C%20wins%20in%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%94%20without%20even%20accounting%20for%20how%20many%20people%20would%20be%20killed%20%E2%80%94%20it%20would%20mean%20that%20fascism%20grew%20stronger%20and%20that%20a%20next%20war%20will%20follow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFascism%20is%20an%20expansive%20ideology.%20You%20build%20fascism%20not%20just%20inside%20your%20country.%20No%2C%20it's%20expansive.%20And%20it%20means%20that%20a%20next%20war%20will%20follow%20and%20a%20next%20war%20will%20follow%20and%20it%20will%20be%20a%20nightmare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-dissident-journalist-elena-kostyuchenko-russia-lose-ukraine-poison-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697576490000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652ec3a196f7540cd05e9e8d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-dissident-journalist-elena-kostyuchenko-russia-lose-ukraine-poison-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Elena%20Kostyuchenko's%20new%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20Love%20Russia%2C%26quot%3B%20compiles%20years%20of%20her%20investigative%20journalism%20alongside%20personal%20narratives%20as%20she%20grapples%20with%20the%20war.%22%2C%