0chain%20of%20inflating%20delivery%20prices.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20suit%20said%20the%20chain%20promised%20low%20delivery%20fees%2C%20but%20then%20%26quot%3Bsecretly%26quot%3B%20increased%20menu%20prices.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEligible%20customers%20will%20receive%20settlement%20via%20cash%20or%20gift%20card%2C%20according%20to%20the%20news%20site%20TopClassActions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchick-fil-a-drive-thru-only-restaurantphotos-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChick-fil-A%3C%2Fa%3E%20reportedly%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehas%20agreed%20to%20shell%20out%20%244.4%20million%20to%20customers%20who%20accused%20the%20chain%20of%20promising%20low-delivery%20fees%2C%20while%20%26quot%3Bsecretly%26quot%3B%20inflating%20menu%20prices%20as%20much%20as%2030%25%20during%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Elegal-news%20site%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftopclassactions.com%2Flawsuit-settlements%2Fconsumer-products%2Ffood%2Fchick-fil-a-settles-class-action-over-delivery-price-increases-for-4-4m%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETopClassActions%3C%2Fa%3E%20first%20reported%20the%20settlement%2C%20which%20comes%20less%20than%20a%20month%20after%20a%20group%20of%20six%20plaintiffs%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20seeking%20class-action%20status%20in%20a%20Georgia%20federal%20court.%20According%20to%20the%20news%20outlet%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20fried%20chicken%20chain%20did%20not%20admit%20guilt%20in%20the%20settlement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20lawsuit%2C%20the%20plaintiffs%20said%20they%20filed%20the%20proposed%20class%20action%20on%20behalf%20of%20themselves%20and%20people%20nationwide%20who%20%26quot%3Bordered%20food%20delivery%20through%20the%20Chick-fil-A%20mobile%20app%20or%20website%2C%20and%20were%20assessed%20higher%20delivery%20charges%20than%20represented.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEligible%20class%20members%20are%20expected%20to