ts%20have%20identified%20concerns%20about%20peace%20and%20security%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20as%20predominantly%20a%20question%20of%20stability%20in%20Taiwan%2C%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%2C%20the%20East%20China%20Sea%2C%20and%20the%20Korean%20Peninsula%20%E2%80%93%20which%20Brendan%20Taylor%20has%20labeled%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.blackincbooks.com.au%2Fbooks%2Ffour-flashpoints%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22%E2%80%9Cfour%20flashpoints%E2%80%9D%20in%20Asia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cfour%20flashpoints%E2%80%9D%20in%20Asia%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20are%20most%20likely%20to%20suddenly%20erupt%20into%20a%20violent%20conflict.%20However%2C%20in%20this%20matrix%2C%20what%20is%20occasionally%20overlooked%20by%20strategists%20and%20analysts%20is%20the%20significance%20of%20the%20India-China%20border%20as%20another%20key%20flashpoint%20in%20Asia%2C%20one%20which%2C%20unlike%20the%20other%20four%20cases%2C%20has%20actually%20witnessed%20violent%20clashes%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20term%20%E2%80%9Cflashpoint%E2%80%9D%20is%20frequently%20used%20as%20shorthand%20for%20any%20geographical%20area%20that%2C%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20reasons%2C%20might%20erupt%20into%20conflict.%20However%2C%20in%20security%20studies%2C%20the%20term%20has%20a%20more%20specific%20meaning.%20US%20Naval%20War%20College%20Professor%20Timothy%20Hoyt%20suggests%20that%20flashpoints%20share%20certain%20elements%3A%20%E2%80%9Cpolitics%2C%20proximity%2C%20and%20paranoia.%E2%80%9D%20First%2C%20they%20must%20be%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20a%20significant%20and%20long-standing%20political%20dispute%3B%20second%2C%20they%20tend%20to%20become%20greater%20concerns%20if%20proximate%20to%20both%20adversaries%3B%20and%20third%2C%20they%20threaten%20to%20involve%20or%20engage%20more%20powerful%20actors%20in%20the%20international%20community%2C%20raising%20the%20possibility%20of%20escalation%20to%20a%20broader%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGoing%20by%20this%20definition%2C%20the%20India-China%20boundary%20fulfills%20all%20the%20criteria%20of%20a%20flashpoint.%20The%20boundary%20dispute%20involves%20a%20longstanding%20territorial%20dispute%20between%20the%20two%20countries%2C%20bringing%20up%20issues%20of%20sovereignty%3B%20the%20two%20countries%20are%20not%20just%20proximate%20but%20are%20also%20nuclear-armed%20neighbours%3B%20and%20lastly%2C%20the%20boundary%20dispute%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20engage%20other%20powerful%20actors%2C%20mainly%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ETense%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cstrong%3Eb%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cb%3Eoundary%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBorder%20tensions%20between%20India%20and%20China%20have%20palpably%20worsened%20in%20recent%20years.%20The%20most%20prominent%20aspect%20of%20this%20is%20the%20ongoing%20Eastern%20Ladakh%20stand-off%20in%20the%20western%20sector%20of%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20(LAC)%2C%20which%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20resolved.%20This%20stand-off%20has%20not%20only%20been%20one%20of%20the%20longest%20but%20it%20also%20follows%20the%20most%20violent%20confrontation%20between%20India%20and%20China%20since%20the%20Sumdorong%20Chu%20crisis%20in%201986%E2%80%9387.%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20troops%20clashed%20in%20June%202020%2C%20leading%20to%20multiple%20casualties%20%E2%80%93%20twenty%20on%20the%20Indian%20side%20and%20an%20undisclosed%20number%20on%20the%20Chinese%20side.%20Since%20then%2C%20there%20has%20been%20little%20progress%20in%20resolving%20the%20stand-off%20despite%20nineteen%20rounds%20of%20Corps%20Commander-level%20talks%20between%20India%20and%20China%2C%20with%20the%20last%20round%20held%20in%20August%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20talks%20have%20made%20some%20progress%20in%20terms%20of%20disengagement%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20creation%20of%20%E2%80%9Cbuffer%20zones%E2%80%9D%20in%20five%20of%20the%20contested%20areas.%20But%20observers%20have%20flagged%20concerns%20about%20the%20current%20disengagement%20only%20involving%20withdrawals%20on%20one%20of%20the%20contested%20border%20areas%2C%20where%20the%20skirmishes%20of%202020%20took%20place.%20Other%20friction%20points%20that%20predate%20the%202020%20clash%20continue%20to%20remain%20tense.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-and-china-are-trapped-in-a-conflict-of-their-own-making%5C%22%3EIndia%C2%A0and%C2%A0China%C2%A0are%20Trapped%20in%20a%20Conflict%20of%20Their%20Own%20Making%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20stand-off%20in%20the%20western%20sector%2C%20tensions%20are%20also%20brewing%20in%20the%20eastern%20sector%20of%20the%20LAC%2C%20in%20the%20Indian%20state%20of%20Arunachal%20Pradesh.%20In%20December%202022%2C%20the%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20militaries%20clashed%20at%20Yangtse%20along%20the%20LAC%20in%20the%20Tawang%20Sector%20in%20Arunachal%20Pradesh.%20Chinese%20efforts%20to%20strengthen%20its%20claims%20in%20the%20area%20have%20led%20Beijing%20to%20adopt%20new%20ways%20and%20means%3A%20building%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fchina-constructing-model-villages-along-lac%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3Exiaokang%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9Cmodel%E2%80%9D%20villages%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20strategic%20areas%2C%20renaming%20places%20and%20issuing%20new%20border%20laws%20that%20India%20sees%20as%20giving%20more%20legal%20cover%20to%20its%20forces.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%202023%20edition%20of%20the%20standard%20map%20of%20China%20issued%20by%20the%20Chinese%20Ministry%20of%20Natural%20Resources%20shows%20the%20entire%20state%20of%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Aksai%20Chin%20region%20%E2%80%93%20both%20of%20which%20India%20sees%20as%20its%20sovereign%20territory%20%E2%80%93%20as%20being%20within%20China%E2%80%99s%20borders.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWider%20conflict%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20politics%20and%20proximity%20clearly%20point%20toward%20the%20India-China%20boundary%20being%20a%20potential%20Indo-Pacific%20flashpoint%2C%20the%20third%20aspect%20remains%3A%20would%20any%20conflict%20risk%20drawing%20in%20other%20powers%2C%20most%20prominently%20the%20US%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20not%20a%20treaty%20ally%20with%20the%20US%2C%20unlike%20its%20partners%20in%20NATO%2C%20which%20means%20Washington%20will%20not%20automatically%20be%20drawn%20into%20any%20conflict%20that%20may%20take%20place%20between%20the%20boundary.%20Yet%2C%20the%20two%20nations%20have%20been%20drawing%20closer%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20to%20a%20large%20extent%2C%20because%20of%20their%20shared%20view%20of%20the%20Chinese%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%202020%20Galwan%20clash%20was%20contained%20at%20the%20bilateral%20level%2C%20later%20reports%20indicated%20that%20the%20US%20subsequently%20provided%20India%20with%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fdelhi-news%2Fus-warned-india-of-chinese-incursion-report-101679422352190.html%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Creal-time%E2%80%9D%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0about%20potential%20Chinese%20actions%20along%20the%20boundary.%20India%20has%20also%20deployed%20US%20weapons%20on%20the%20LAC.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F19190135%2Fchina-india-ladakh-disengagement.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22957%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F19190135%2Fchina-india-ladakh-disengagement.png%20957w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F19190135%2Fchina-india-ladakh-disengagement-300x183.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-511372%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22584%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFILE%20IMAGE%3A%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20troops%20and%20tanks%20disengage%20from%20the%20banks%20of%20Pangong%20lake%20area%20in%20Eastern%20Ladakh.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%2FIndian%20Army%20handout%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20February%202023%2C%20the%20US%20Senate%20introduced%20a%20bipartisan%C2%A0resolution%20reaffirming%20the%20state%20of%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20as%20Indian%20territory%20while%20positing%20that%20China%E2%80%99s%20claim%20over%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20is%20part%20of%20its%20%E2%80%9Cincreasingly%20aggressive%20and%20expansionist%20policies.%E2%80%9D%20Besides%2C%20the%20US%20has%20also%20been%20maintaining%20a%20close%20watch%20on%20the%20developments%20along%20the%20LAC%20since%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20Eastern%20Ladakh%20standoff%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20the%202021%20US%20Department%20of%20Defense%20(DoD)%20report%20noted%20that%20a%20100-home%20civilian%20village%20has%20been%20constructed%20%E2%80%9Cinside%20disputed%20territory%20between%20the%20Tibet%20Autonomous%20Region%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20state%20in%20the%20eastern%20sector%20of%20the%20LAC.%E2%80%9D%20The%202022%20DoD%20report%20suggests%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20People%E2%80%99s%20Republic%20of%20China%20seeks%20to%20prevent%20border%20tensions%20from%20causing%20India%20to%20partner%20more%20closely%20with%20the%20United%20States.%20The%20PRC%20officials%20have%20warned%20US%20officials%20to%20not%20interfere%20with%20the%20PRC%E2%80%99s%20relations%20with%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%202022%20National%20Defense%20Strategy%20of%20the%20US%20categorically%20outlines%20that%20Washington%20will%20support%20%E2%80%9Cally%20and%20partner%20efforts%20to%20address%20acute%20forms%20of%20gray%20zone%20coercion%20from%20the%20PRC%E2%80%99s%20campaigns%20to%20establish%20control%20over%20the%20East%20China%20Sea%2C%20Taiwan%20Strait%2C%20South%20China%20Sea%2C%20and%20disputed%20land%20borders%20such%20as%20with%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20increasing%20threat%20presented%20by%20China%20has%20prompted%20New%20Delhi%20and%20Washington%20to%20work%20together%20to%20counter%20the%20issue.%20The%20two%20countries%20have%20incrementally%20strengthened%20their%20bilateral%20partnership%2C%20including%20enhanced%20defense%20interoperability%20and%20information-sharing%2C%20especially%20for%20early%20warning%20systems.%20For%20China%2C%20there%20is%20a%20strong%20sense%20of%20unease%20about%20the%20growing%20India-US%20proximity%2C%20especially%20in%20terms%20of%20defense%20ties.%20As%20former%20Indian%20foreign%20secretary%20Vijay%20Gokhale%20argues%2C%20the%20Chinese%20suspect%20that%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20will%20lean%20to%20the%20United%20States%20to%20derive%20benefits%20and%20that%20China%20will%20become%20the%20target%20of%20containment.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20and%20the%20US%20have%20also%20boosted%20collaboration%20at%20the%20%E2%80%9Cminilateral%E2%80%9D%20level%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcasi.sas.upenn.edu%2Fiit%2Faditimalhotra%5C%22%3Ethrough%20the%20Indo-Pacific-focused%20Quad%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20which%20includes%20Japan%20and%20Australia%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20US%20and%20India%20%E2%80%93%20and%20in%20other%20fora%20with%20the%20aim%20of%20balancing%20China%2C%20though%20the%20efforts%20are%20not%20officially%20described%20as%20such.%20At%20the%20global%20level%2C%20the%20growing%20intensity%20of%20the%20US-China%20strategic%20rivalry%20increases%20the%20salience%20of%20the%20India-China%20border%20flashpoint%2C%20particularly%20when%20considered%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20evolving%20Indo-Pacific%20security%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIncreasing%20volatility%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhy%20has%20the%20India-China%20boundary%20been%20overlooked%2C%20particularly%20as%20a%20flashpoint%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific%2C%20until%20recently%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20assumption%20is%20that%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20is%20broadly%20seen%20as%20a%20maritime%20region.%20The%20four%20other%20flashpoints%20are%20also%20maritime%20areas%20and%20have%20multiple%20stakeholders%2C%20while%20the%20India-China%20Border%20is%20land-based%20and%2C%20more%20specifically%2C%20has%20generally%20been%20treated%20as%20a%20bilateral%20issue.%20The%20other%20potential%20reason%20is%20that%2C%20for%20long%2C%20the%20international%20community%20perceived%20India%20as%20a%20power%20limited%20to%20South%20Asia%20and%20as%20a%20counterweight%20solely%20against%20Pakistan.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20border%20dispute%20with%20China%2C%20which%20also%20witnessed%20a%20war%20in%201962%2C%20received%20relatively%20little%20global%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20past%20decade%20has%20seen%20attitudes%20changing.%20The%20causes%20for%20this%20shift%20are%20India%E2%80%99s%20growing%20economic%20and%20material%20heft%2C%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20strong%20counter%20to%20China%E2%80%99s%20military%20activism%20in%20the%20Himalayas%20(Doklam%20in%202017%20and%20Eastern%20Ladakh%20and%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20since%202022)%20and%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20region%2C%20and%20the%20Western%20belief%20that%20India%20can%20play%20a%20bigger%20role%20in%20balancing%20China%2C%20just%20as%20the%20US%20relies%20on%20Japan%20and%20South%20Korea%20to%20help%20it%20with%20balancing%20in%20the%20East%20Asian%20maritime%20flashpoints.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHaving%20replaced%20peaceful%20co-existence%20with%20armed%20co-existence%2C%20the%20increased%20volatility%20at%20the%20India-China%20border%20is%20making%20it%20even%20harder%20to%20foresee%20a%20permanent%20solution%20to%20the%20territorial%20dispute%20in%20the%20immediate%20future.%20Given%20the%20uncertainties%20and%20the%20prevailing%20conditions%20along%20the%20India-China%20boundary%2C%20the%20possibility%20of%20yet%20another%20flare-up%20remains%20very%20real.%20Any%20such%20situation%20will%20be%20detrimental%20to%20the%20security%20and%20stability%20of%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20region%2C%20and%20have%20implications%20for%20every%20other%20stakeholder%2C%20beyond%20just%20India%20and%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20first%20appeared%20in%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcasi.sas.upenn.edu%2Fiit%2Famritajash%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fcasi.sas.upenn.edu%2Fiit%2Fudayandas%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1697624538309000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1hHpUZI4jlNYa6b8cG0NpI%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcasi.sas.upenn.edu%2Fiit%2Fudayandas%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndia%20in%20Transition%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20a%20publication%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20the%20Advanced%20Study%20of%20India%20(University%20of%20Pennsylvania).%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EAmrita%20Jash%20is%20an%20Assistant%20Professor%20at%20the%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmanipal.edu%2Fgir%2Fdepartment-faculty%2Ffaculty-list%2Fdr-amrita-jash%2F_jcr_content.html%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EDepartment%20of%20Geopolitics%20and%20International%20Relations%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%2C%20Manipal%20Academy%20of%20Higher%20Education%20(Institution%20of%20Eminence)%2C%20India.%20She%20can%20be%20reached%20at%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Famritajash%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%40amritajash%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%20on%20Twitter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697545809000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F17115001%2FIndustry-Conflict-Politics-China-India-Flags-5628865.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fthough-often-overlooked-india-china-border-is-a-key-flashpoint-in-the-indo-pacific%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20dominant%20view%20among%20security%20analysts%20is%20that%20Taiwan%2C%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%2C%20the%20East%20China%20Sea%2C%20and%20the%20Korean%20Penins