20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F17155829%2FAAAAQS22Qzsni_-e2z_xlsvyUOg3augZko4lOnzteFMsTkCpCLzY58rXY-Wb6sYG060y7tHywfPpTobKJkeG10D72YGW97RGtvAUEalOSmNJWFR8KjmVyTPi7ih-20_HpvQdugfoDzNksKoqyVHITZsGVA7x.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20review%20contains%20spoilers.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMike%20Flanagan%E2%80%99s%20latest%20and%20final%20Netflix%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.netflix.com%2Ftudum%2Farticles%2Fmidnight-club-cast-mike-flanagan-flanaverse%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Flanaverse%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0series%20before%20he%20moves%20to%20Amazon%20Prime%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Fall%20of%20the%20House%20of%20Usher%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20is%20a%20macabre%20reinterpretation%20of%20Edgar%20Allan%20Poe%E2%80%99s%20classic%20tale%20of%20the%20same%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMuch%20like%20his%20previous%20well-received%20series%20like%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Haunting%20of%20Hill%20House%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(based%20on%20the%20novel%20by%20Shirley%20Jackson)%20and%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Haunting%20of%20Bly%20Manor%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(based%20on%20Henry%20James%E2%80%99s%20gothic%20novella%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Turn%20of%20the%20Screw%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20the%20horror%20auteur%20uses%20several%20of%20Poe%E2%80%99s%20stories%20as%20a%20foundation%20to%20weave%20together%20a%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESuccession%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0meets%C2%A0%3Cem%3EFinal%20Destination%3C%2Fem%3E-style%20Gothic%20series%20with%20a%20piercing%20commentary%20on%20several%20modern%20ills%20%E2%80%93%20particularly%20unbridled%20corporate%20greed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20course%20of%20eight%20episodes%2C%20Fortunato%20Pharmaceuticals%20CEO%20Roderick%20Usher%20(Bruce%20Greenwood)%20explains%20to%20Assistant%20US%20Attorney%20C.%20Auguste%20Dupin%20(Carl%20Lumbly)%20how%20and%20why%20each%20of%20his%20six%20adult%20children%20died%20in%20the%20last%20two%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20deal%20with%20the%20devil%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201979%2C%20we%20learn%20that%20Roderick%20and%20his%20twin%20sister%2C%20Madeline%20(Mary%20McDonnell)%2C%20made%20a%20Faustian%20deal%20at%20a%20bar%20with%20a%20devilish%20and%20ageless%20figure%20named%20Verna%20(played%20to%20perfection%20by%20Carla%20Gugino)%20to%20secure%20a%20powerful%20and%20affluent%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20catch%3F%20When%20it%E2%80%99s%20time%20for%20Roderick%20and%20Madeline%20to%20die%2C%20their%20entire%20family%20goes%20before%20them.%20The%20whole%20bloodline%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%3Cem%3Enevermore%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20post-murder%20haze%20from%20killing%20Fortunato%20boss%20Rufus%20Griswold%2C%20the%20siblings%20(the%20younger%20versions%20played%20by%20Zach%20Gilford%20and%20Willa%20Fitzgerald)%20consent%20to%20these%20terms.%20The%20series%20reveals%20that%20Verna%20struck%20similar%20deals%20with%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%2C%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20John%20Francis%20Queeny%20(founder%20of%20Monsanto)%20the%20Koch%20family%2C%20the%20Rockefellers%2C%20the%20Vanderbilts%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%20that%20follow%20that%20fateful%20New%20Years%E2%80%99%20night%2C%20the%20two%20siblings%20go%20on%20to%20make%20billions%20on%20the%20back%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98painkiller%E2%80%99%20called%20Ligodone%20%E2%80%93%20a%20highly%20addictive%20pill%20that%20is%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20opioid%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20made-up%20substance%20parallels%20Oxycodone%2C%20the%20actual%20pain%20reliever%20more%20than%2013%20million%20Americans%20are%20addicted%20to%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.addictioncenter.com%2Fopiates%2Foxycodone%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOxycodone%2520Abuse%2520Statistics%26amp%3Btext%3DAccording%2520to%2520the%2520United%2520States%2Cyoung%2520as%252012%2520years%2520old.%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20United%20States%20Department%20of%20Justice%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%98consequence%E2%80%99%3F%20Millions%20addicted%20and%20dead%20from%20overuse.%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20House%20of%20Usher%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0heavily%20underscores%20the%20ethical%20abyss%20that%20some%20pharmaceutical%20corporations%20venture%20into%2C%20where%20profit%20sometimes%20takes%20precedence%20over%20patients%E2%80%99%20well-being%2C%20prompting%20viewers%20to%20contemplate%20the%20harrowing%20repercussions%20of%20corporate%20ambition%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20real%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%E2%80%99s%20no%20such%20thing%20as%20a%20painkiller.%20Imagine%20if%20we%20put%20that%20on%20the%20bottle.%20I%20bet%20I%20could%E2%80%99ve%20still%20sold%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20Roderick%20says%20towards%20the%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20death%20comes%20knocking%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEach%20Usher%20(barring%20Lenore%2C%20the%20granddaughter)%20is%20amoral%2C%20cruel%20and%20selfish%2C%20so%20much%20so%20that%20watching%20their%20consecutive%20gruesome%20deaths%20leaves%20one%20wincing%20over%20the%20brutality%20without%20necessarily%20feeling%20sympathy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20kids%20%E2%80%93%20immature%20manchild%20Frederick%20(Henry%20Thomas)%2C%20wannabe-GOOP%20health%20guru%20Tamerlane%20(Samantha%20Sloyan)%2C%20unethical%20surgeon%20Victorine%20(T%E2%80%99Nia%20Miller)%2C%20drug-addicted%20and%20philandering%20Napoleon%20(Rahul%20Kohli)%2C%20PR%20maven%20Camille%20(Kate%20Siegel)%2C%20and%20hedonistic%20Prospero%20(Sauriyan%20Sapkota)%20%E2%80%93%20are%20named%20after%20characters%20from%20Poe%E2%80%99s%20works.%20They%20all%20receive%20an%20individual%20episode%20that%20loosely%20aligns%20with%20a%20renowned%20tale.%20These%20include%20%E2%80%98The%20Tell-Tale%20Heart%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20Masque%20of%20the%20Red%20Death%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98The%20Black%20Cat%E2%80%99%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20clock%20begins%20to%20tick%20early%20for%20Prospero%2C%20the%20youngest.%20Desperate%20to%20prove%20his%20worth%20to%20his%20father%2C%20the%2020-something%20throws%20an%20exclusive%20masquerade-style%20orgy%20at%20one%20of%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20company%E2%80%99s%20abandoned%20facilities%20which%20was%20meant%20to%20be%20demolished%20as%20it%20was%20a%20storage%20site%20for%20illegal%20toxic%20waste.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20here%20that%20we%20witness%20the%20first%20very%20grisly%20%E2%80%93%20and%20most%20brutal%20%E2%80%93%20consequence%20of%20the%20deal%20with%20Verna%2C%20who%20arrives%20at%20the%20scene%20of%20debauchery%20to%20warn%20the%20youngest%20Usher%20about%20his%20plans%20for%20the%20evening%20of%20having%20a%20rain-soaked%20night%20to%20remember.%20One%20gut-churning%20scene%20later%2C%20Verna%20finally%20leaves%20the%20site%20after%20placing%20a%20white%20mask%20on%20the%20chemically-melted%20face%20of%20Prospero%20in%20a%20room%20full%20of%20over%2070%20fused%20and%20melted%20bodies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20comeuppances%20continue%20with%20a%20murderous%20black%20cat%2C%20a%20descent%20to%20madness%2C%20a%20lab%20animal%20hitting%20back%2C%20a%20paralysed%20bisection%20and%20more.%20The%20true%20horror%20stems%20from%20the%20reactions%20of%20the%20Ushers%20to%20the%20deaths%2C%20as%20they%20continue%20to%20march%20towards%20their%20foreshadowed%20fates.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20comparison%2C%20while%20Verna%20may%20be%20the%20one%20dealing%20the%20death%20cards%20%E2%80%93%20and%20may%20just%20be%20the%20devil%20herself%20%E2%80%93%20there%20is%20still%20a%20humaneness%20to%20her%20as%20she%20goes%20about%20collecting%20souls.%20The%20biggest%20evidence%20of%20this%20is%20her%20care%20for%20Lenore%2C%20who%20she%20puts%20to%20sleep%20after%20telling%20her%20that%20her%20mother%20changes%20millions%20of%20lives%20for%20the%20better%20in%20the%20future%20through%20a%20foundation%20in%20Lenore%E2%80%99s%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98It%E2%80%99s%20time%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20who%20exactly%20is%20Verna%3F%20An%20anagram%20for%20%E2%80%98Raven%E2%80%99%2C%20Gugino%E2%80%99s%20mysterious%20character%20is%20Flanagan%E2%80%99s%20nod%20to%20Poe%E2%80%99s%20famous%20poem%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20Raven%E2%80%99.%20As%20Poe%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9C%5Bthe%20raven%E2%80%99s%5D%20eyes%20have%20all%20the%20seeming%20of%20a%20demon%E2%80%99s%20that%20is%20dreaming%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20line%20that%20links%20to%20Verna%E2%80%99s%20own%20demonic%20nature.%20In%20the%20grand%20tapestry%20of%20the%20narrative%2C%20Verna%20serves%20as%20both%20an%20observer%20and%20a%20catalyst.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20even%20Roderick%20and%20Madeline%E2%80%99s%20time%20is%20up.%20After%20Roderick%20confesses%20to%20Dupin%20that%20he%20knowingly%20climbed%20mountains%20of%20bodies%20to%20gain%20wealth%20and%20power%2C%20he%20and%20Madeline%20are%20crushed%20to%20death%20as%20their%20childhood%20home%20caves%20in%20%E2%80%93%20as%20it%20did%20in%20Poe%E2%80%99s%20original%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20ruthlessness%20of%20the%20family%20also%20spills%20over%20into%20the%20character%20played%20by%20Mark%20Hamill%20(known%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98Pym%20Reaper%E2%80%99)%2C%20an%20unscrupulous%20lawyer%20and%20general%20all-purpose%20fixer%20for%20the%20Ushers.%20Arthur%20Pym%20eventually%20even%20turns%20down%20a%20deal%20with%20Verna.%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20no%20collateral.%20Collateral%20is%20leverage%2C%20and%20I%20won%E2%80%99t%20be%20leveraged%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20tells%20her.%20It%E2%80%99s%20delightful%20to%20see%20Hamill%20taking%20on%20an%20atypical%20part%2C%20the%20first%20of%20hopefully%20many%20such%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFlanagan%20has%20undisputedly%20won%20himself%20a%20loyal%20fanbase.%20He%20also%20co-created%202022%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Midnight%20Club%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20adapted%20two%20different%20Stephen%20King%20novels%20into%20films%3A%202017%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Cem%3EGerald%E2%80%99s%20Game%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0and%202019%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Cem%3EDoctor%20Sleep%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20coming%20months%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%