C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ffact-check-israel-govt-falsely-claims-photos-of-slain-4-year-old-in-gaza-are-of-a-doll%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Device%20Seizures%20Are%20Making%20a%20Mockery%20of%20The%20Supreme%20Court's%20Landmark%20Privacy%20Ruling%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F24204013%2FIMG_4150.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20piece%20was%20first%20published%20on%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20India%20Cable%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%C2%A0The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2Fp%2Fsame-sex-marriage-ruling-due-on-tuesday%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3Eclick%20here%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20first%20week%20of%20November%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20will%20hear%20petitions%20by%20five%20academics%20%E2%80%93%20Ram%20Ramaswamy%2C%20Deepak%20Malghan%2C%20Sujata%20Patel%2C%20Mukul%20Kesavan%20and%20Madhava%20Prasad%2C%20along%20with%20the%20Foundation%20for%20Media%20Professionals%20%E2%80%93%20which%20urge%20the%20court%20to%20lay%20down%20guidelines%20for%20the%20exercise%20of%20police%20and%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%E2%80%99%20powers%20to%20search%20and%20seize%20personal%20digital%20devices.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202017%2C%20a%20nine-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20court%20spoke%20in%20one%20voice%20as%20it%20held%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%20to%20be%20a%20constitutionally%20guaranteed%20fundamental%20right%20implicit%20in%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20and%20indeed%2C%20a%20synoptic%20reading%20of%20various%20other%20enumerated%20rights%20in%20the%20constitution.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20held%20that%20privacy%20in%20the%20digital%20age%20cannot%20be%20enforced%20or%20protected%20as%20an%20individual%20interest%20at%20all%20unless%20it%20is%20consecrated%20and%20fortified%20as%20a%20fundamental%20right.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20was%20aware%20of%20the%20non-foreseeability%20of%20harms%20that%20arise%20out%20of%20a%20violation%20of%20the%20right%20to%20privacy.%20The%20court%20also%20elaborated%20on%20the%20various%20forms%20and%20facets%20of%20the%20right%2C%20including%20the%20privacy%20of%20correspondence%2C%20privacy%20as%20autonomy%2C%20and%20privacy%20as%20self-determination%20over%20personal%20information.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20modern%20notions%20of%20privacy%20in%20the%20digital%20age%20use%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98privacy%E2%80%99%20as%20shorthand%20to%20refer%20to%20a%20bundle%20of%20several%20concomitant%20rights%20over%20personal%20information%20%E2%80%93%20the%20right%20of%20access%2C%20the%20right%20of%20erasure%2C%20the%20right%20to%20have%20a%20say%20in%20the%20manner%20of%20its%20processing%2C%20the%20right%20of%20accuracy%2C%20the%20right%20of%20control%20of%20third-party%20access%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20this%20universally%20celebrated%20ruling%20has%20had%20little%20impact%20on%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20behaviour.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20mobile%20phone%20is%20the%20treasure%20trove%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20entire%20private%20life.%20But%20neither%20parliament%20nor%20any%20of%20the%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20have%20seen%20the%20need%20or%20desirability%20to%20evolve%20any%20guidelines%20on%20how%20and%20when%20they%20could%20search%20the%20contents%20of%20a%20suspect%E2%80%99s%20mobile%20phone%3B%20or%20of%20its%20seizure%2C%20of%20the%20extraction%20of%20data%20from%20it%20or%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20it%20is%20produced%20or%20proved%20before%20a%20trial%20court.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Finterview-justice-srikrishna-data-protection-police-raid%5C%22%3EInterview%3A%20%E2%80%98Police%20Cannot%20Touch%20the%20Data%20on%20Your%20Computer%20Without%20Your%20Consent%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20Arnab%20Goswami%20handed%20in%20his%20phone%20and%20access%20to%20its%20data%20to%20the%20police%2C%20little%20did%20he%20know%20that%20his%20private%20communications%20in%20an%20instant%20messaging%20app%20would%20be%20disclosed%20to%20the%20entire%20world.%20It%20was%20the%20same%20with%20Rhea%20Chakraborty.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20if%20one%20were%20to%20take%20an%20unsympathetic%20view%20of%20Goswami%20and%20Chakraborty%2C%20given%20that%20at%20that%20time%20they%20were%20both%20%E2%80%98accused%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20question%20also%20pertains%20to%20the%20privacy%20of%20others%20who%20had%20been%20in%20correspondence%20with%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMobile%20phones%20also%20contain%20data%20about%20other%20people%20%E2%80%93%20contact%20information%2C%20text%20messages%2C%20and%20emails.%20When%20police%20search%20a%20mobile%20phone%2C%20they%20gain%20access%20to%20this%20third-party%20data%20without%20the%20knowledge%20or%20consent%20of%20the%20other%20people%20involved.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20process%20by%20which%20law%20enforcement%20gains%20access%20to%20a%20phone%20may%20require%20answering%20a%20few%20questions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDoes%20the%20search%20of%20a%20phone%20require%20a%20judicial%20warrant%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECan%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20search%20be%20limited%20by%20that%20warrant%3F%20For%20instance%2C%20if%20there%20is%20reasonable%20suspicion%20that%20a%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20a%20crime%20had%20been%20hatched%20in%20a%20WhatsApp%20group%20chat%2C%20can%20investigators%20check%20the%20subject%E2%80%99s%20communications%20in%20other%20groups%2C%20or%20other%20instant%20messaging%20or%20email%20communications%2C%20without%20further%20reason%20to%20believe%20that%20those%20are%20relevant%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20the%20scope%20of%20that%20search%20can%20indeed%20be%20limited%2C%20what%20measures%20would%20be%20needed%20to%20ensure%20that%20those%20limits%20are%20adhered%20to%3F%20Will%20the%20suspect%20be%20given%20a%20right%20to%20be%20present%20when%20the%20contents%20are%20being%20examined%2C%20and%20to%20object%20to%20the%20transgression%20of%20those%20limits%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20related%20question%20is%20whether%20the%20police%20should%20notify%20third-party%20data%20subjects%20when%20their%20data%20is%20being%20searched.%20This%20would%20give%20third-party%20data%20subjects%20the%20opportunity%20to%20challenge%20the%20search%20or%20to%20take%20steps%20to%20protect%20their%20privacy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FJoGxsZrhAGY%3Fsi%3DWOMy7l10aCZkFfcn%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20addition%20to%20privacy%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20would%20also%20have%20an%20opportunity%20to%20examine%20the%20matter%20from%20the%20point%20of%20view%20of%20the%20right%20against%20self-incrimination%2C%20protected%20under%20Article%2020(3)%20of%20the%20constitution%20%E2%80%93%20also%20known%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98right%20to%20silence%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20issue%20arises%20in%20several%20ways%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20production%20of%20devices%20by%20persons%20accused.%20However%2C%20the%20concern%20has%20generally%20been%20about%20the%20compulsion%20to%20divulge%20credentials%2C%20such%20as%20a%20password%20or%20a%20PIN.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20a%20divergence%20of%20views%20among%20courts%20in%20other%20jurisdictions%20on%20this%20aspect.%20Some%20have%20held%20that%20police%20cannot%20compel%20a%20person%20to%20disclose%20their%20password%2C%20even%20if%20they%20have%20obtained%20a%20warrant.%20These%20courts%20have%20reasoned%20that%20disclosing%20a%20password%20is%20a%20testimonial%20act%20that%20is%20protected%20by%20the%20right%20against%20self-incrimination.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20there%20are%20also%20judgments%20that%20hold%20that%20police%20can%20compel%20a%20person%20to%20disclose%20their%20password%20if%20they%20have%20obtained%20a%20warrant.%20These%20courts%20have%20reasoned%20that%20disclosing%20a%20password%20is%20not%20a%20testimonial%20act%2C%20but%20rather%20a%20physical%20act%20that%20is%20similar%20to%20providing%20a%20fingerprint%20or%20DNA%20sample.%20The%20Karnataka%20high%20court%20took%20this%20view%20last%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20guidelines%20that%20the%20petitions%20seek%20also%20involve%20the%20protection%20of%20privileged%20communications%2C%20such%20as%20between%20spouses%2C%20between%20an%20attorney%20and%20a%20client%2C%20or%20a%20doctor%20and%20patient%2C%20and%20perhaps%20more%20pertinently%2C%20information%20that%20constitutes%20journalistic%20privilege%20or%20source%20secrecy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20last%20but%20not%20the%20least%20concern%20is%20the%20return%20of%20devices%20seized%20during%20a%20search%20operation.%20Although%20Section%20451%20of%20the%20CrPC%20empowers%20the%20court%20to%20release%20seized%20devices%20once%20data%20has%20been%20extracted%2C%20in%20practice%2C%20the%20devices%20are%20detained%20eternally.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPrivacy%20also%20includes%20the%20basic%20notion%20that%20the%20owner%20has%20been%20deprived%20access%20to%20the%20phone%20and%20its%20contents%2C%20which%20are%20required%20to%20carry%20on%20with%20life%20in%20the%20digital%20age.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20chooses%20to%20lay%20down%20guidelines%20addressing%20some%20of%20these%20concerns%2C%20it%20would%20not%20only%20be%20%E2%80%98filling%20the%20gap%E2%80%99%2C%20but%20will%20in%20many%20ways%20herald%20a%20new%20age%20where%20there%20is%20some%20realisation%20of%20the%20landmark%202017%20ruling.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fprasanna%5C%22%3EPrasanna%20S.%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20an%20advocate-on-record%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20assists%20the%20petitioners%20in%20%3C%2Fem%3ERam%20Ramaswamy%20%26amp%3B%20Ors%20V%20Union%20of%20India%20WP(Crl)%20138%2F2021%3Cem%3E%2C%20which%20is%20mentioned%20in%20this%20piece.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697535285000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F24204013%2FIMG_4150.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdevice-seizures-making-a-mockery-of-landmark-privacy-ruling%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20mobile%20phone%20is%20the%20treasure%20trove%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20entire%20private%20life.%20But%20neither%20parliament%20nor%20any%20of%20the%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20have%20seen%20the%20need%20or%20desirability%20to%20evolve%20any%20guidelines%20on%20how%20and%20when%20they%20could%20search%20the%20contents%20of%20a%20suspect%E2%80%99s%20mobile%20phone.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdevice-seizures-making-a-mockery-of-landmark-privacy-ruling%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India's%20Supreme%20Court%20refuses%20to%20legalise%20same-sex%20marriage%22%2C%22c